----

Nachtwachtlaan, Amsterdam
High-rise living with a breathtaking, panoramic view over Amsterdam, right next to the Rembrandtpark! This wonderfully bright and perfectly laid-out 2-room apartment of 61 m² offers a living experience that is rare within the Ring road. The combination of impressive height, abundant natural light, and unobstructed views gives this property a distinct semi-penthouse feel. From the living room, the bedroom, and the balcony, you can look out for miles over the greenery of the park, the Zuidas business district, and the iconic city skyline. Thanks to its elevated position, you will enjoy absolute peace, privacy, and an unobstructed view without any direct look-ins every single day.

Layout
Ground floor: Representative, communal entrance with intercom system, mailboxes, video intercom, staircase, and a double elevator system. On the ground floor, there is a convenient private storage unit (ideal for bicycles). In the secured underground parking garage, you have the luxury of your own private parking space.

The spacious and bright living room forms the vibrant heart of the home. Thanks to the wall-to-wall windows and the ceiling height, there is plenty of space for a comfortable seating area and a cozy dining corner. The adjacent open-plan kitchen is modern and fully equipped with all desired built-in appliances.

The bedroom is also generously sized and features built-in wardrobes. You can step directly onto the spacious balcony from both the bedroom and the living room. This is the ultimate spot to unwind after a busy workday and enjoy the afternoon and evening sun slowly sinking behind the horizon.

The neat bathroom is equipped with a comfortable walk-in shower and a washbasin.

Surroundings & Accessibility
The complex is fantastically located: you can walk straight from the central hall into the green Rembrandtpark. In the summer, this park feels like your own backyard, offering plenty of space for sports, relaxation, pleasant walks, and events.

Here you live in peace and privacy, while the dynamic energy of the city remains within easy reach. Trendy hotspots in De Baarsjes, Oud-West, the Jan Evertsenstraat, and the Vondelpark are just a short bike ride away. For your daily groceries, you can visit various supermarkets (AH, Aldi, Lidl) and specialty shops in the neighborhood.

Accessibility is flawless. Within 10 to 15 minutes of cycling, you are at Dam Square. Lelylaan Station (train, metro, tram) is just around the corner, and the tram stops at Surinameplein and Derkinderenstraat are also within walking distance. By car, you can reach the Ring A10 within a few minutes, heading towards Schiphol, Utrecht, or Haarlem.

Key Features
- Living area: 61 m² (measurement report available);
- Premium comfort: Sweeping, unobstructed views;
- Balcony: Spacious balcony;
- Sustainability: Equipped with double glazing;
- Parking & Storage: Includes a private parking space in the secured garage and two storage units;
- Ground lease (Erfpacht): Ground lease for both the apartment and the parking space has been paid off up to and including 15-06-2094;
- Healthy VvE (HOA): Professionally managed by Delair Vastgoedbeheer;
- Service charges: € 167.76 per month (apartment) + € 27.96 per month (parking space). The advance payment for heating costs is € 90.- per month;
